²⁸ This remark is interesting, as connected with the experiment which was the occasion of Bacon's death. On a cold morning in the spring of 1626, he descended from his coach at the bottom of Highgate Hill, bought a hen of a poor woman, and stuffed it with snow. The chill, to which he was thus exposed, brought on an attack ol what we should now call bronchitis, of which he died on the 9th of April.
